[[Image:Sindelfingen Goldbergturm.jpg|thumb|Goldbergturm]] The '''Goldbergturm''' is a 51 metre high [[water tower]] on the Goldberg (''gold mountain'') at {{coord|48|42|06|N|9|01|03|E|}} in [[Sindelfingen]], [[Germany]]. The Goldbergturm was built in 1963 and has in its basket, besides a [[reservoir (water)|water reservoir]], a restaurant from which a stairway runs to its open-air [[observation deck]].
